Let's add some use cases covering functionalities of ModuleBook 3.5.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix typo referring to ModuleBook as AddressBook under use cases

commitResults.messageBody:
Tasks can be marked as done using tags or editing the description.

This is very inconvenient.

Let's add a done command to allow a task to be marked as done.

This is more convenient.

Tasks marked as Done stay Done. A new task has to be created if one wants to redo the task.

This is inconvenient if one wants to mark a task as not done to highlight that the task needs to be redone.

Let's add a NotDone command.

This allows a task to be toggled between done and not done.

commitResults.messageBody:
The task done status is shown as a string on the GUI.

This can make the task details too wordy.

Let's implement colour coding for done status.

This makes it easier to see if a task is done or not done.
